    "text": {
      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Steinar H. Gunderson</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"https://github.com/sesse\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/e/e5/SteinarHGunderson.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:SteinarHGunderson.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Sesse <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Steinar H. Gunderson</b>, (Sesse)<br />\na Norwegian computer scientist and software engineer, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Debian\">Debian</a> developer and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Demoscene\">ex-demoscener</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>.\nWhile currently affiliated with the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oracle_Corporation\">Oracle Corporation</a> in the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MySQL\">MySQL</a> optimizer team, he previously worked at <a href=\"/index.php?title=Google&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Google (page does not exist)\">Google</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Switzerland\">Switzerland</a> on projects such as <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPv6\">IPv6</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snappy_%28software%29\">Snappy</a>, and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_Images\">Search by Image</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. \nHe holds a master in CS from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norwegian_University_of_Science_and_Technology\">Norwegian University of Science and Technology</a> in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trondheim\">Trondheim</a> on the topic of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Music_information_retrieval\">music information retrieval</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>. \nSteinar H. Gunderson has a wide range of interests spanning from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_signal_processing\">DSP</a> and computer chess to <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/High-level_programming_language\">high-level languages</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_architecture\">networking architecture</a>. He has contributed to various <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_and_open-source_software\">FOSS</a> projects <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Computer_Chess\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Computer Chess</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2007_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2007 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2020_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2020 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Computer_Chess\">Computer Chess</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Steinar_H._Gunderson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Computer Chess\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>In 2007, Sesse published the unofficial <a href=\"/CTG\" title=\"CTG\">CTG</a> specification (ChessBase Opening Tree of Games) <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>.\nHe is author of <b>remoteglot</b> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>, a program used to use a <a href=\"/Category:UCI\" title=\"Category:UCI\">UCI compatible chess engine</a> to analyze chess games, \nincluding live online relay. It is used for his live chess analysis website, known as <b>Sesse</b> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>.\nHe has further written the <a href=\"/UCI\" title=\"UCI\">UCI</a> compliant engine <a href=\"/Stupid\" title=\"Stupid\">Stupid</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>, hosts <a href=\"/Nalimov_Tablebases\" title=\"Nalimov Tablebases\">Nalimov Tablebases</a> and <a href=\"/Syzygy_Bases\" title=\"Syzygy Bases\">Syzygy Bases</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>, \nand is contributor to the <a href=\"/Stockfish\" title=\"Stockfish\">Stockfish</a> project <sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Steinar_H._Gunderson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steinar H. Gunderson</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://descriptors.sesse.net/\">Musical descriptors: An assessment of psychoacoustical models in the presence of lossy compression</a></i>. M.Sc. thesis, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norwegian_University_of_Science_and_Technology\">Norwegian University of Science and Technology</a>, advisor <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.ntnu.edu/employees/jantro\">Jan Tro</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/c/Colitti:Lorenzo\">Lorenzo Colitti</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steinar H. Gunderson</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/k/Kline:Erik\">Erik Kline</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/r/Refice:Tiziana\">Tiziana Refice</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-642-12334-4_15\">Evaluating IPv6 adoption in the Internet</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/pam/pam2010.html\">Passive and Active Measurement Conference</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=2cn46OkAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Henrik Stewénius</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steinar H. Gunderson</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/p/Pilet:Julien\">Julien Pilet</a> (<b>2012</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-642-33709-3_48\">Size Matters: Exhaustive Geometric Verification for Image Retrieval</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/eccv/eccv2012-2.html\">European Conference on Computer Vision</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Steinar H. Gunderson</a> (<b>2014</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.fosdem.org/2014/schedule/event/movit/\">Movit: High-speed, high-quality video filters on the GPU</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FOSDEM\">FOSDEM</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.fosdem.org/2014/\">2014</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://movit.sesse.net/movit-fosdem2014.pdf\">pdf</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/GPU\" title=\"GPU\">GPU</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Steinar_H._Gunderson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2007_...\">2007 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Steinar_H._Gunderson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2007 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=1690\">(Experimental) 64-bit Rybka on Linux</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sesse</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, July 10, 2007</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=2319\">CTG specification</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sesse</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, September 30, 2007</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=12312\">Changes to tablebase.sesse.net</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sesse</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, August 27, 2009</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Steinar_H._Gunderson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=66797&amp;start=246\">Re: 7-men Syzygy attempt</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sesse</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 02, 2018&#160;» <a href=\"/Syzygy_Bases\" title=\"Syzygy Bases\">Syzygy Bases</a>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=66797&amp;start=328\">Re: 7-men Syzygy attempt</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sesse</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 22, 2018</li></ul></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=67432&amp;start=3\">Re: Ryzen 2 and BMI2?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sesse</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 15, 2018&#160;» <a href=\"/BMI2\" title=\"BMI2\">BMI2</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=71537\">Does computer chess sponsorship exist?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sesse</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 13, 2019</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2020_...\">2020 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Steinar_H._Gunderson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2020 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=72910\">Why is MultiPV so slow?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sesse</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 25, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Principal_Variation#MultiPV\" title=\"Principal Variation\">MultiPV</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=73126&amp;start=11\">Re: SIMD methods in TT probing and replacement</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sesse</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 20, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/SIMD_and_SWAR_Techniques\" title=\"SIMD and SWAR Techniques\">SIMD and SWAR Techniques</a>, <a href=\"/Transposition_Table\" title=\"Transposition Table\">Transposition Table</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Steinar_H._Gunderson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.sesse.net/\">Steinar H. Gunderson - Sesse.net</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/sesse\">sesse (Steinar H. Gunderson) · GitHub</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://git.sesse.net/\">git.sesse.net Git</a>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://git.sesse.net/?p=remoteglot;a=summary\">remoteglot/summary</a> </li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://git.sesse.net/?p=stupid\">Stupid, a chess AI</a></li></ul></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://analysis.sesse.net/\">analysis.sesse.net</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://tablebase.sesse.net/\">tablebase.sesse.net</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Steinar_H._Gunderson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/sesse\">sesse (Steinar H. Gunderson) · GitHub</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text